						<div class="postbody">In addition, a CPU cycle counter would allow your code to turn off the screen early and take advantage of the post-render scanline.
<br />
<br />If you make a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fangame" class="postlink">fan game</a> that uses the original game's copyrighted characters, you probably won't be able to sell it. But the good news is that you don't need to worry about selling it. So you can go ahead and put in FME-7 or a similarly powerful mapper, as most players will experience it through an emulator anyway.</div>

					
